history.text: Hi there!
Hey, how are you doing today?
I'm doing pretty good. Seems like we both get the documents this time.
Have you seen Bruce Almighty before?
Yes, we do.
Yeah I have what about you?
I have. It's a pretty funny movie and I rather enjoyed it.
The movie has a great cast of actors and actresses especially for that time.
I enjoyed it quite a bit as well
Yeah it had a real A-list of comedy actors and actresses. Morgan Freeman really stole the show in my opinion.
Yeah I especially liked Morgan Freeman and Jim Carrey in the movie they both fit their respective roles well.
I'm really surprised that it's not rated particularly well it seems.
I guess it's just not one of those critic appeasing films.
Yeah I know, when I saw the reviews I was very surprised. I thought it would be rated much higher but maybe in 2003 it was not so popular I can not recall
I think it was one of those films that doesn't make huge waves but it is a decent film. I've definitely seen worse movies.
Yeah I have as well. It is one of those comedies that serves its purpose.
Yeah, I guess it just didn't gel with critics. I enjoyed it though. Has that early 2000's lesson of learning to appreciate what you have.
Yes that seems to be the message.
Jim Carrey is doing his typical delivery so maybe people were just a little tired of that at that point.
I especially like when Bruce starts to have the encounters with god
Yes. The interactions between Carrey and Freeman really carry the film.
Yeah I still remember some of those iconic scenes and they still make me laugh.
Freeman does a lot of subtlety as God and goes for more of a soft spoken performance that has a lot of wisdom behind it.
Yeah a Carrey is more over the top and both of their styles together worked
The relationship between Bruce and Grace was also an interesting story line
Yeah, as it starts out Bruce is kind of shallow and doesn't really see what he has with her but he learns to appreciate what she means for him.
Yeah Morgan Freeman really helps him understand how important she is to his life.
Plus I really love Jennifer Aniston as an actress.
Yeah I have always liked her.
I was just a big fan of this cast
Yeah, it's really shocking to me that it wasn't well received. But it is 2003. They didn't have the cinema train wrecks we have now for comparison.
And I think we're done. Been nice talking with you
That is very true
Have a good day!
Yeah you as well have a good one
